^d @e@2hondo717: Now let me briefly review the scoring of doubled contracts. If you are vulnerable down 1 is @E@3200, and every trick thereafter is 300, so 200, 500, 800, 1100, etc.  If you are not vul, the sequence is 100 for down 1, then 300, 500, 800, 1100. So, at equal vulnerability, you do better beating them 3 than bidding a game because non-vul down 3 is 500, and your game is somewhere around 420-450. And vul down 3 is 800, and your game is around 620-650. If the opponents are vul and you are not, then you only need beat them 2. Because down 2 vul is 500, and your game is 420 or so. 

If you are vul and the opps are not, then you have to beat them 4, because down 4 is 800, down 3 is 500, and your game is worth 620 or so. Basically remember at equal vul must beat them 3, when you are they not, must beat them 4. when they are you not, must beat them 2. It is reasonably important to know that, because it helps you decide when to sacrifice, and when to double their sacrifices.

Now, I will address the cuebids in he next panel.|
