^B@2hondo717: Now, I like to explain the support double. The most common situation where a support double applies is this type of auction. I open 1 of a minor and partner bids 1 of a major. The next person overcalls after responder's one of a major call. This gives me an extra bid, double, that is not available if there was not an overcall. As with takeout doubles and negative doubles, the idea here is that it is unlikely that opener will have a hand suitable for a penalty double. So, this frees up the double to have some other meaning, assuming you are willing to give up the penalty double in this type of auction. |
