^B@2hondo717: Therefore, a double over the overcall is known as a "support double", meaning opener has exactly 3 card support for responder's major. A raise of the major (in this case my bidding 2 hearts) shows 4 card support. This allows responder to more precisely gauge how high it is safe to bid, because responder knows exactly how many trumps we have between the 2 hands. Therefore, it is up to responder to make the final decision as to how high to bid, which is why I said aggie should bid 2@H, since she is the one who knows we have an 8 card fit. For all I know, we have a 7 card fit.|
